WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:05.305
Cheers is filmed before
a live studio audience.

00:05.305 --> 00:06.973
Hey, Sam!

00:06.973 --> 00:08.341
Hey, Woody. Is it all right

00:08.341 --> 00:10.310
if I hang some Christmas
decorations in here?

00:10.310 --> 00:13.313
Sure. Boy, is it that time again?

00:13.313 --> 00:16.315
Wow, Christmas comes earlier
every year, doesn't it?

00:16.315 --> 00:18.818
I think if you check, Sam,

00:19.319 --> 00:22.822
it always comes on the 25th of December.

00:22.822 --> 00:24.324
Of course, of course, of course.

00:24.324 --> 00:27.277
Thank you, Woody, thank you.

00:27.277 --> 00:29.779
Oh, look at that, will ya?

00:29.779 --> 00:30.663
Nice Rudolph.

00:30.663 --> 00:32.115
I made him myself.

00:32.115 --> 00:33.116
No kidding?

00:33.116 --> 00:35.118
You know, uh, Rudolph is my favorite guy

00:35.118 --> 00:36.619
in the Christmas songs.

00:36.619 --> 00:38.004
Yeah.

00:38.004 --> 00:39.756
You know, apparently
then, Woody, you're unaware

00:39.756 --> 00:42.258
that the story of Rudolph
the Red-Nosed Reindeer

00:42.258 --> 00:43.259
is one of the most unrealistic,

00:43.760 --> 00:44.761
and therefore potentially damaging

00:44.761 --> 00:46.262
in all of children's music.

00:46.262 --> 00:48.264
It gives them a horribly
distorted view of reality.

00:48.264 --> 00:50.767
Yeah, but you gotta admit,
it's easy to whistle.

00:50.767 --> 00:52.268
Look, I'm serious.

00:52.268 --> 00:54.938
You know, first the other reindeer tease

00:54.938 --> 00:56.306
and then ostracize him.

00:56.306 --> 01:00.226
And then when his abnormality
proves of service, they use him.

01:02.112 --> 01:03.396
But then do they allow him to play

01:03.396 --> 01:04.397
in their stupid reindeer games?

01:04.397 --> 01:05.397
BOTH: Yes.

01:05.397 --> 01:06.399
Oh, no, no, no,

01:06.399 --> 01:07.901
I know how the song goes.

01:07.901 --> 01:08.902
In fact,

01:08.902 --> 01:10.904
not only do Donner, Blitzen, et al,

01:10.904 --> 01:13.907
not love him and laugh out with glee,

01:13.907 --> 01:16.292
but they doubly despise the
bulbous-nosed little wimp.

01:17.994 --> 01:19.329
Well, I gotta be off.

01:19.329 --> 01:20.713
(cheerful): Happy Holidays!

01:22.966 --> 01:26.419
(piano plays)

01:26.886 --> 01:29.172
? Making your way in the world today ?

01:29.172 --> 01:32.175
? Takes everything you've got ?

01:32.175 --> 01:35.178
? Taking a break from all your worries ?

01:35.178 --> 01:38.181
? Sure would help a lot ?

01:38.181 --> 01:44.737
? Wouldn't you like to get away? ?

01:44.737 --> 01:46.239
? Sometimes you want to go ?

01:46.239 --> 01:51.744
? Where everybody knows your name ?

01:51.744 --> 01:56.749
? And they're always glad you came ?

01:56.749 --> 01:58.751
? You want to be where you can see ?

01:58.751 --> 02:01.754
? Our troubles are all the same ?

02:01.754 --> 02:06.759
? You want to be where
everybody knows your name ?

02:06.759 --> 02:09.262
? You want to go where people know ?

02:09.262 --> 02:11.764
? People are all the same ?

02:11.764 --> 02:16.269
? You want to go where
everybody knows your name. ?

